50|$|In the United Kingdom, free <b>TV</b> <b>Licences</b> are {{available}} to those aged over 75. The BBC absorbs {{the cost of this}} subsidy for over-75s until at least 2020, estimated at £750m. The concession covers the whole household, so that even if just one member of the household is over 75, then a free <b>TV</b> <b>Licence</b> may be applied for to cover all the residents.The Isle of Man has an identical scheme funded by the Isle of Man Department of Social Care.|$|R
